  "prompt": "How does Samsung Stylus Pen work?",
  "response": "Samsung Stylus Pens (S Pen) work through the following key technologies:\n\n1. Electromagnetic Resonance (EMR) Technology\n- Uses electromagnetic field between pen and device screen\n- Allows precise tracking and pressure sensitivity\n- No battery required in most stylus models\n\n2. Pressure Sensitivity\n- Detects varying levels of pressure when writing or drawing\n- Allows line thickness and intensity variations\n- Typically supports multiple pressure levels (e.g., 4096 levels)\n\n3. Bluetooth Connectivity\n- Some advanced S Pen models have Bluetooth\n- Enables remote control functions\n- Allows air gestures and actions without touching screen\n\n4. Sensors and Features\n- Tilt detection for more natural writing angles\n- Proximity sensing to activate pen-related functions\n- Button for additional controls\n\n5. Screen Interaction\n- Uses specialized digitizer layer in compatible Samsung devices\n- Provides high-precision tracking\n- Supports palm rejection technology\n\n6. Charging\n- Newer models with Bluetooth can be charged\n- Some pens charge wirelessly when inserted into device\n\n7. Materials\n- Typically made with conductive materials\n- Designed for smooth screen interaction\n- Ergonomically shaped for comfortable use\n\nThese technologies enable Samsung Stylus Pens to provide precise, responsive digital writing and drawing experiences.",
